<node TEXT="is a platform" LOCALIZED_STYLE_REF="AutomaticLayout.level,2" ID="ID_277684985" CREATED="1552672519931" MODIFIED="1553529437273"><richcontent TYPE="NOTE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <font size="10.0pt" face="Verdana,sans-serif" color="black">Any hardware or software environment in which a program runs, is known as a platform. Since Java has a runtime environment (</font><font color="black" face="Verdana,sans-serif">JRE</font><font color="black" face="Verdana,sans-serif" size="10.0pt">) and API, it is called a platform. </font>
    </p>
    <p>
      <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); display: inline !important; float: none"><font color="rgb(0, 0, 0)" face="verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif" size="13px">There are two types of platforms software-based and hardware-based. Java provides a software-based platform.</font></span>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
