<node TEXT="classLoader" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_564537477" CREATED="1553838918625" MODIFIED="1553869170578"><richcontent TYPE="DETAILS" HIDDEN="true">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Classloader is a subsystem of JVM which is used to load class files. Whenever we run the java program, it is loaded first by the classloader. There are three built-in classloaders in Java.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classpath_(Java)">class path </a><br/>&#160;<a href="https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/environment/paths.html">class path-oracle</a>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
<node TEXT="Bootstrap classloader" ID="ID_1725907544" CREATED="1553839108958" MODIFIED="1553839194236"><richcontent TYPE="DETAILS" HIDDEN="true">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      This is the first classloader which is the super class of Extension classloader. It loads the rt.jar file which contains all class files of Java Standard Edition like java.lang package classes, java.net package classes, java.util package classes, java.io package classes, java.sql package classes etc.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
<node TEXT="Extension classloader" ID="ID_1379298971" CREATED="1553839121054" MODIFIED="1553839208588"><richcontent TYPE="DETAILS" HIDDEN="true">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      &#160;This is the child classloader of Bootstrap and parent classloader of System classloader. It loades the jar files located inside $JAVA_HOME/jre/lib/ext directory.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
